default1.1
default&#xa0; 
defaultRelational Research is just beginning a three year project seeking to understand 
defaultschool academic 
defaultsuccess
default by focusing on 
defaultstakeholder relationships
default. 
defaultSchools involve a wide 
defaultrange of internal and external stakeholders and there is a matrix of relationships in any school (and from school to school): these include students, teachers, support staff, educational specialists, administrators, governors, parents, local communities, f
defaultaith communities (in some instances), local and central government and society at large.
default 
defaultRelational Research
default and Relationships Foundation 
defaultendeavour
default 
defaultto influence public policy and organisational pr
defaultactice with a relational agenda
default.
default 
defaultThe aim is to build ‘relati
defaultonal capital’ in the lives of families and communities through the way organisations and structures are
default 
defaultarranged
default, and through the
default goals they set for themselves.
default&#xa0;
default1.2
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe want 
defaultto understand the means by which relational practice can be fostered in schools. 
defaultWe wish to 
defaultdetermine ways in which schools and students can be assessed for their relational understanding and competence.
default&#xa0;
default1.3
default&#xa0; 
defaultWe are interested in the ways in which the interconnection of key stakeholders intersect at critical stages in a student’s school ca
defaultreer, establishing ways of evaluating how such impact is manifested, with a view to transferring emergent understanding to other students, and to thus support successful outcomes.
default We provide practical help to schools to intervene and encourage greater prox
defaultimity between the key stakeholders in education and thus improve student outcomes. We have worked 
defaultsuccessfully i
defaultn 
defaultvarious
default 
defaultpublic service settings such as primary health care and 
defaultprisons
default.
